00:00:04.089 --> 00:00:05.089
5 Mysteries Science Can’t Explain

00:00:05.089 --> 00:00:11.740
Science is dedicated to solving riddles, answering
questions and generally demystifying the vast

00:00:11.740 --> 00:00:12.740
universe.

00:00:12.740 --> 00:00:17.680
So far, we managed to explain and understand
a lot of things.

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:22.880
We’ve peered into the furthest reaches of
the universe and delved into the exciting

00:00:22.880 --> 00:00:24.699
world of atoms.

00:00:24.699 --> 00:00:29.910
We managed to understand the basic building
blocks of life while building a civilization

00:00:29.910 --> 00:00:33.600
capable of learning about uninhabited planets.

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:37.670
The last few centuries have been especially
good for science.

00:00:37.670 --> 00:00:43.480
In the 17th century, Isaac Newton solved the
ancient controversy over the nature of forces

00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:46.110
and motion with his three laws.

00:00:46.110 --> 00:00:51.719
In the 18th, Ben Franklin figured out a lot
about electricity.

00:00:51.719 --> 00:00:57.969
In the 19th, Darwin explained the diversity
of species, Maxwell revealed the physics of

00:00:57.969 --> 00:01:02.860
light, and Mendeleyev defined the families
of chemical elements.

00:01:02.860 --> 00:01:10.369
Finally, in the 20th century, we had Einstein,
who figured out all sorts of stuff, including

00:01:10.369 --> 00:01:11.549
gravity.

00:01:11.549 --> 00:01:17.620
Still, there is a long way ahead of us and
a lot of mysteries left for the 21st century

00:01:17.620 --> 00:01:18.950
to solve.

00:01:18.950 --> 00:01:19.950
Hi!

